			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Carbon_cycle.jpg" class="mw-file-description" title="Image 5This diagram of the fast carbon cycle shows the movement of carbon between land, atmosphere, and oceans in billions of metric tons of carbon per year. Yellow numbers are natural fluxes, red are human contributions, white are stored carbon. (from Carbon dioxide in Earth&#39;s atmosphere)"><img alt="Image 5This diagram of the fast carbon cycle shows the movement of carbon between land, atmosphere, and oceans in billions of metric tons of carbon per year. Yellow numbers are natural fluxes, red are human contributions, white are stored carbon. (from Carbon dioxide in Earth&#39;s atmosphere)" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d5/Carbon_cycle.jpg/120px-Carbon_cycle.jpg" decoding="async" width="120" height="101" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d5/Carbon_cycle.jpg/180px-Carbon_cycle.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d5/Carbon_cycle.jpg/240px-Carbon_cycle.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2600" data-file-height="2192" /></a></span></div>
