			<div class="gallerytext"><span class="switcher-label" style="display:none"><span class="randomSlideshow-sr-only">Image 30</span></span>Earth's energy budget (in W/m<sup>2</sup>) determines the climate. It is the balance of incoming and outgoing <a href="/wiki/Radiation" title="Radiation">radiation</a> and can be measured by satellites. The <a href="#Earth&#39;s_energy_imbalance_(EEI)">Earth's energy imbalance</a> is the "net absorbed" energy amount and grew from +0.6&#160;W/m<sup>2</sup> (2009 est.) to above +1.0&#160;W/m<sup>2</sup> in 2019. (from <b><a href="/wiki/Earth%27s_energy_budget" title="Earth&#39;s energy budget">Earth's energy budget</a></b>)</div>
