			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Tyndalls_setup_for_measuring_radiant_heat_absorption_by_gases_annotated.svg" class="mw-file-description" title="Image 47John Tyndall&#39;s ratio spectrophotometer (drawing from 1861) measured how much infrared radiation was absorbed and emitted by various gases filling its central tube. (from History of climate change science)"><img alt="Image 47John Tyndall&#39;s ratio spectrophotometer (drawing from 1861) measured how much infrared radiation was absorbed and emitted by various gases filling its central tube. (from History of climate change science)" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a9/Tyndalls_setup_for_measuring_radiant_heat_absorption_by_gases_annotated.svg/120px-Tyndalls_setup_for_measuring_radiant_heat_absorption_by_gases_annotated.svg.png" decoding="async" width="120" height="112" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a9/Tyndalls_setup_for_measuring_radiant_heat_absorption_by_gases_annotated.svg/180px-Tyndalls_setup_for_measuring_radiant_heat_absorption_by_gases_annotated.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a9/Tyndalls_setup_for_measuring_radiant_heat_absorption_by_gases_annotated.svg/240px-Tyndalls_setup_for_measuring_radiant_heat_absorption_by_gases_annotated.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="960" data-file-height="893" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext"><span class="switcher-label" style="display:none"><span class="randomSlideshow-sr-only">Image 47</span></span><a href="/wiki/John_Tyndall" title="John Tyndall">John Tyndall</a>'s <a href="/wiki/Spectrophotometry" title="Spectrophotometry">ratio spectrophotometer</a> (drawing from 1861) measured how much infrared radiation was absorbed and emitted by various gases filling its central tube. (from <b><a href="/wiki/History_of_climate_change_science" title="History of climate change science">History of climate change science</a></b>)</div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Mauna_Loa_CO2_monthly_mean_concentration.svg" class="mw-file-description" title="Image 48Atmospheric CO2 concentration measured at Mauna Loa Observatory in Hawaii from 1958 to 2023 (also called the Keeling Curve). The rise in CO2 over that time period is clearly visible. The concentration is expressed as μmole per mole, or ppm. (from Carbon dioxide in Earth&#39;s atmosphere)"><img alt="Image 48Atmospheric CO2 concentration measured at Mauna Loa Observatory in Hawaii from 1958 to 2023 (also called the Keeling Curve). The rise in CO2 over that time period is clearly visible. The concentration is expressed as μmole per mole, or ppm. (from Carbon dioxide in Earth&#39;s atmosphere)" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c5/Mauna_Loa_CO2_monthly_mean_concentration.svg/120px-Mauna_Loa_CO2_monthly_mean_concentration.svg.png" decoding="async" width="120" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c5/Mauna_Loa_CO2_monthly_mean_concentration.svg/180px-Mauna_Loa_CO2_monthly_mean_concentration.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c5/Mauna_Loa_CO2_monthly_mean_concentration.svg/240px-Mauna_Loa_CO2_monthly_mean_concentration.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="708" data-file-height="708" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext"><span class="switcher-label" style="display:none"><span class="randomSlideshow-sr-only">Image 48</span></span>Atmospheric CO<sub style="font-size: 80%;vertical-align: -0.35em">2</sub> concentration measured at <a href="/wiki/Mauna_Loa_Observatory" title="Mauna Loa Observatory">Mauna Loa Observatory</a> in Hawaii from 1958 to 2023 (also called the <a href="/wiki/Keeling_Curve" title="Keeling Curve">Keeling Curve</a>). The rise in CO<sub>2</sub> over that time period is clearly visible. The concentration is expressed as μmole per mole, or <a href="/wiki/Parts-per_notation" title="Parts-per notation">ppm</a>.  (from <b><a href="/wiki/Carbon_dioxide_in_Earth%27s_atmosphere" title="Carbon dioxide in Earth&#39;s atmosphere">Carbon dioxide in Earth's atmosphere</a></b>)</div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:NORTH_POLE_Ice_(19626661335).jpg" class="mw-file-description" title="Image 49Sea ice reflects 50% to 70% of incoming sunlight, while the ocean, being darker, reflects only 6%. As an area of sea ice melts and exposes more ocean, more heat is absorbed by the ocean, raising temperatures that melt still more ice. This is a positive feedback process. (from Causes of climate change)"><img alt="Image 49Sea ice reflects 50% to 70% of incoming sunlight, while the ocean, being darker, reflects only 6%. As an area of sea ice melts and exposes more ocean, more heat is absorbed by the ocean, raising temperatures that melt still more ice. This is a positive feedback process. (from Causes of climate change)" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/64/NORTH_POLE_Ice_%2819626661335%29.jpg/120px-NORTH_POLE_Ice_%2819626661335%29.jpg" decoding="async" width="120" height="80" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/64/NORTH_POLE_Ice_%2819626661335%29.jpg/180px-NORTH_POLE_Ice_%2819626661335%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/64/NORTH_POLE_Ice_%2819626661335%29.jpg/240px-NORTH_POLE_Ice_%2819626661335%29.jpg 2x" data-file-width="7360" data-file-height="4912" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext"><span class="switcher-label" style="display:none"><span class="randomSlideshow-sr-only">Image 49</span></span>Sea ice reflects 50% to 70% of incoming sunlight, while the ocean, being darker, reflects only 6%. As an area of sea ice melts and exposes more ocean, more heat is absorbed by the ocean, raising temperatures that melt still more ice. This is a positive feedback <a href="/wiki/Ice%E2%80%93albedo_feedback" title="Ice–albedo feedback">process</a>. (from <b><a href="/wiki/Causes_of_climate_change" title="Causes of climate change">Causes of climate change</a></b>)</div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:20210331_Global_tree_cover_loss_-_World_Resources_Institute.svg" class="mw-file-description" title="Image 50The rate of global tree cover loss has approximately doubled since 2001, to an annual loss approaching an area the size of Italy. (from Causes of climate change)"><img alt="Image 50The rate of global tree cover loss has approximately doubled since 2001, to an annual loss approaching an area the size of Italy. (from Causes of climate change)" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1f/20210331_Global_tree_cover_loss_-_World_Resources_Institute.svg/120px-20210331_Global_tree_cover_loss_-_World_Resources_Institute.svg.png" decoding="async" width="120" height="76" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1f/20210331_Global_tree_cover_loss_-_World_Resources_Institute.svg/180px-20210331_Global_tree_cover_loss_-_World_Resources_Institute.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1f/20210331_Global_tree_cover_loss_-_World_Resources_Institute.svg/240px-20210331_Global_tree_cover_loss_-_World_Resources_Institute.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="1184" data-file-height="750" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext"><span class="switcher-label" style="display:none"><span class="randomSlideshow-sr-only">Image 50</span></span>The rate of global tree cover loss has approximately doubled since 2001, to an annual loss approaching an area the size of Italy. (from <b><a href="/wiki/Causes_of_climate_change" title="Causes of climate change">Causes of climate change</a></b>)</div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
