<div style="text-align: center;"><figure class="mw-halign-center" typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:NASA-28yrs-Arctic-Warming.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4d/NASA-28yrs-Arctic-Warming.jpg/625px-NASA-28yrs-Arctic-Warming.jpg" decoding="async" width="625" height="353" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4d/NASA-28yrs-Arctic-Warming.jpg/938px-NASA-28yrs-Arctic-Warming.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4d/NASA-28yrs-Arctic-Warming.jpg/1250px-NASA-28yrs-Arctic-Warming.jpg 2x" data-file-width="1268" data-file-height="716" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure><div style="margin: 0.5em 0.25em 0.85em;"><div><span style="font-size:120%"><a href="/wiki/Climate_change_in_the_Arctic" title="Climate change in the Arctic">Climate change in the Arctic</a></span></div><small>Credit:&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://svs.gsfc.nasa.gov/vis/a000000/a003600/a003672/index.html">NASA</a></small></div></div><div class="center" style="width:auto; margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto;">the <b><a href="/wiki/Climate_change_in_the_Arctic" title="Climate change in the Arctic">Arctic temperature trend</a></b> between August 1981 and July 2009. Due to global warming, which is exacerbated at the <a href="/wiki/Arctic" title="Arctic">Arctic</a>, there's a significant warming over this 28 year period.</div><div class="noprint" style="text-align:right; margin-top:0.5em;"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1129693374"><div class="hlist"><ul><li><b><a href="/wiki/Portal:Climate_change/panorama" class="mw-redirect" title="Portal:Climate change/panorama">More selected pictures</a></b></li></ul></div></div>
